      <h3>Generic overflow dropdown button</h3>
      <p>The generic overflow dropdown button displays an arrow or menu button by default. When the button is pressed, the menu
        appears. Pressing an option on the menu navigates to further settings for that option.</p>
      <h3>Segmented dropdown button</h3>
      <p>A segmented dropdown has two sections: the current state and the dropdown arrow icon. Pressing the current state will
        cause that state’s action to fire within the screen. Pressing the dropdown arrow will display all the state options.
        Selecting one will change the displayed state.</p>
      <h3>Editable segmented dropdown button</h3>
      <p>This button has a segmented dropdown, where the displayed state is text editable, such as a font size picker. Pressing
        the current state causes both that state’s action to fire and makes the displayed state editable. Pressing the arrow
        displays all the state options.</p>
